# ===========================
# Git Commit Message Template 
# (for Study Repositories, v3)
# ===========================
# Field format:
#    <type>: <subject>
# - type:
#    add        : add new content (note, code, section)
#    update     : improve existing content (clarify, expand, revise)
#    fix        : correct errors (typo, formula, link)
#    refactor   : content restructuring (naming, order, layout)
#    remove     : delete unnecessary content
#    config     : repository configuration or metadata
# - subject: concise description (5â€“8 words)
#   - For `add`, `update`, `fix`, `remove`: noun phrase
#   - For `refactor`, `config`: sentence-like noun phrase
# ===========================
# Examples:
# - add: expectation of random vector
# - update: conditional expectation examples
# - fix: typo in CLT section
# - refactor: probability structure
# - refactor: note hierarchy
# - config: .gitignore
# - config: .gitmessage template
# ===========================

